    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-background-set-construction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To perform ORA, three essential inputs are required: a collection of pathways (or custom metabolite sets), a list of metabolites of interest, and a background or reference set of compounds... The background set contains all molecules which can be detected in the experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses background set construction and its critical importance, but describes it as 'all molecules which can be detected in the experiment' (assay-specific), not as 'filtering a complete pathway database to exclude experimental detection lists.' The paper's recommendation is to use an assay-specific background set (all identified compounds in the dataset), not to filter a pathway database. The framing in the card inverts the actual method: the paper recommends using the experimental detection list to define the background, not excluding it.",
