      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Both removal of compounds at random and non-DA compounds from the background set resulted in a decrease in the proportion of SEP (p \u2264 0.1) as compared to using 100% of the compounds in the background set.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates that background set size (proxy for coverage) directly affects number of significant enriched pathways (SEPs), which is consistent with coverage-dependent statistical artifacts.",
