    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-set-composition-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To perform ORA, three essential inputs are required: a collection of pathways (or custom metabolite sets), a list of metabolites of interest, and a background or reference set of compounds... The background set contains all molecules which can be detected in the experiment... Specify a realistic background set based on the analytical platform used in the experiment. A conservative yet practical approach is to use all the metabolites that have been identified in the assay.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper extensively discusses background-set construction, validation, and its critical impact on ORA results. The research question aligns with the paper's core finding that background-set specification is 'an often-overlooked step' with profound effects on ORA outcomes.",
