    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pathway-coverage-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We investigated the effect of using a nonspecific background set, consisting of all unique compounds present in the KEGG organism-specific pathway set, compared to an assay-specific background set, consisting only of compounds identified and present in the abundance matrix of each dataset... We calculated the overlap coefficient (OC) for each of the 23 pairs of equivalent pathways.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does compute overlap metrics (overlap coefficient) between pathway databases and datasets, but the framing differs: the paper's focus is on validating ORA parameter choices (background set, pathway database selection) rather than assessing 'statistical completeness' of pathway databases per se. The paper examines background-set effects and pathway-database concordance, not per-pathway coverage validation as a pre-ORA step.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009105",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
