      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "All simulations were performed using Python (v 3.8). Simulations with an element of randomisation were repeated 100 times, and results are reported as the mean of 100 random samplings of the simulation, alongside the standard error of the mean.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses Python v3.8 for simulations and specifies specific package versions (scipy, bioservices v1.7.1, MetaboAnalyst 4.0, KEGG REST API). However, the paper does not present environment setup as a primary research task or skill to be taught\u2014it is mentioned only in Methods. The card frames this as a standalone skill/workflow, but the paper treats it as infrastructure for executing the actual research (ORA parameter sensitivity analysis). The paper does not discuss Jupyter notebooks or provide environment configuration files (requirements.txt, environment.yml, setup.py).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009105",
