    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/statistical-distribution-visualization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The factors examined are: the background set, selection of differential metabolites, pathway database choice, organism-specific pathway sets, metabolite misidentification, and chemical bias of the assay... we vary the inputs, each time comparing to the original or standard settings, thus demonstrating the effect of these choices on the output lists of significant pathways.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly examines how input coverage (background set), detection thresholds (differential metabolite selection), and methodological choices (pathway database, organism-specificity) alter outcomes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1371_journal_pcbi_1009105",
