      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce two new statistics: the pathway loss rate and the pathway gain rate... The pathway loss rate refers to the proportion of SEPs present at 0% misidentification that are no longer present at f % misidentification, and the pathway gain rate refers to the number of SEPs not originally present at 0% misidentification which become significant at f % misidentification.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly assesses false-positive and false-negative rates (pathway gain and loss rates) across conditions of varying metabolite misidentification.",
